title: Stanford's Owusu broke the Internet with this catch
text:
Stanford's Owusu broke the Internet with this catch By Sean Walker | Posted Oct 16th, 2015 @ 11:04am 7  
FRANCIS OWUSU'S WORLD — For those who didn't stay up with #Pac12AfterDark on Thursday, they missed a fun game in Stanford's 56-35 win over UCLA. 
They also missed a great play by the Cardinal, forcing everyone else in college football to battle the rest of the season for second place. 
"SportsCenter Top 10" for days. No, weeks. No, the year. 
Shut it down, folks, the Internet has been won. 
Here are some of our favorite moments from the Internet. Stanford receiver makes catch of the year 
College football has already seen a lot of fantastic catches this year in an age where quarterbacks have better touch and defenses are allowed to give them more time than ever before. 
Stanford wide receiver Francis Owusu topped them all Thursday night. 
With his arms stretched outward, Owusu hauled in a touchdown pass from Cardinal quarterback Kevin Hogan and pinned it against UCLA defensive back Jaleel Wadood, maintaining possession of it to the ground. 
Let's repeat that again: He used the defensive back to pin the ball and help him catch the touchdown pass. 
Here's ESPN's Joe Tessitore trying to fathom how the catch happened. 
The only thing that topped Owusu's catch, though, was Stanford coach David Shaw's reaction to it.
